summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Six & 32/100 ($6.32) Dollars out of the Dearborn Street Condemnation Fund authorized by Ordinance No. 13320, as a refund to Mrs. M. J. Wisby, who purchased Lot four (4), Block Forty-seven (47), Rainier Boulevard Garden Addition, at sale on August 5, 1908, which lot it has been subsequently discovered does not exist.
